<div class="page-header">Nix Primer</div>
<section id="Overview">
  <div class="p">
    Nix is a relatively lightweight, portable, and elegant package
    management system. 'Nix' may also refer to the functional language
    used to describe packages. Here, we provide an overview for both
    sufficient to get one started using nix to develop 'micro
    distributions' for use in development and production environments.
  </div>
  <div class="p">
    The primer is organized into a series of 'trails'. The trails are
    largely independent, though later trails may build on the general
    knowledge discussed in and make the occasional reference to
    previous trails.
  </div>
</section>
<section id="Trails">
  <h1>Trails</h1>
  <div class="p">
    <ul>
      <li>
	<em><a href="/documentaiton/nix-primer/Micro-Distributions">Micro-Distributions</a></em>:
	Walk through the "how" of building a simple
	'micro-distribution' to better understand the "why" of nix.
      </li>
      <li>
        <em><a href="/documentation/nix-primer/Key-Features">Key
	Features</a></em>: A quick demonstration of the key features
	of the nix package management system.
      </li>
      <li>
	<em><a href="/documentation/nix-primer/Building-Packages">Building
	Packages</a></em>: Walk through using nix-expressions to build
	packages.
      </li>
      <li>
	<em><a href="/documentation/nix-primer/Gotchas-and-Oddities">Gotchas
	and Oddities</a></em>: Despite the overall elegance, the nix
	language has it's warts.
      </li>
      <li>
	<em><a href="/documentation/nix-primer/Development-Integeration">Development
	Integration</a></em>: Patterns to integrate nix with
	development.
      </li>
      <li>
	<em><a href="/documentation/nix-primer/Basic-Admin">Basic
	Admin</a></em>: Run through basic nix administration.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>
